A glitch in the vaccine rollout in Gauteng. Pensioners are urged NOT to go to vaccination sites. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Senior citizens in Gauteng are being urged not to go to vaccination centres on Monday. The province's health department says the main focus will be on vaccinating healthcare workers and visiting old age homes. READ: COVID-19 in SA: Level 1 regulations flouted The province is expecting its first batch of 138,000 jabs.